Great unity of nation under banner of independence called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 10 (KCNA) -- A recent joint meeting of the DPRK government, political parties and organizations officially proposed to set this year as a "year of independence and great unity of the nation". Papers here today say that the proposal reflects the patriotic stand and will of the Workers' Party of Korea and the DPRK government to accelerate national reunification with the concerted strength of the nation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A signed article of Rodong Sinmun says:
   To hold high the banner of independence and great unity of the nation is a basic guarantee for saving the Korean nation from disasters and reunifying the country with the strength of the Korean nation itself.
   If the Korean nation fails to get united, losing independence and depending on or following outside forces, it will face holocaust of war. But, if it goes united in defence of sovereignty, its life and soul, as the DPRK does, it will check and frustrate any war provocation moves of the outside forces and open the door for national reunification.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It cannot be overlooked that the South Korean authorities are openly begging for indefinite presence of U.S. troops in South Korea at a time when the independence of the nation should be emphasized and defended as never before.  Such action cannot be allowed as it will result in  turning the Korean peninsula into a place of rowdyism of aggressors for eser after betraying the dignity and sovereignty of the nation.
   Anyone who really wants inter-Korean reconciliation, national unity and reunification  should take the road of national independence, not depending on outside forces.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Minju Joson in a signed article says that the South Korean authorities and political parties should adopt a resolute decision to discard flunkeyism and dependence on outsiders, make a switchover from the policy of anti-north confrontation to a policy of reconciliation with the north and take the road of independence and great unity of the nation.
